proaches dissident intellectuals have taken to politics.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / History & Theory.2bisacsh  aEthics, Philosophy, Political philosophy, Political studies.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCentral European University Press eBook-Package 2013-1998z978311078055040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9786155211614423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9786155211614/original  a978-3-11-078055-0  Central European University Press eBook-Package 2013-1998c1998d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles